8691/// Determines how the size should be computed to achieve the one of the
8692/// visibility mode for the scrollbars.
8693#[derive(Debug, Eq, PartialEq, Ord, PartialOrd, Hash, Clone, Copy)]
8694#[non_exhaustive]
8695#[doc(alias = "GtkPolicyType")]
8696pub enum PolicyType {
8697    /// The scrollbar is always visible. The view size is
8698    ///   independent of the content.
8699    #[doc(alias = "GTK_POLICY_ALWAYS")]
8700    Always,
8701    /// The scrollbar will appear and disappear as necessary.
8702    ///   For example, when all of a [`TreeView`][crate::TreeView] can not be seen.
8703    #[doc(alias = "GTK_POLICY_AUTOMATIC")]
8704    Automatic,
8705    /// The scrollbar should never appear. In this mode the
8706    ///   content determines the size.
8707    #[doc(alias = "GTK_POLICY_NEVER")]
8708    Never,
8709    /// Don't show a scrollbar, but don't force the
8710    ///   size to follow the content. This can be used e.g. to make multiple
8711    ///   scrolled windows share a scrollbar.
8712    #[doc(alias = "GTK_POLICY_EXTERNAL")]
8713    External,
8714    #[doc(hidden)]
8715    __Unknown(i32),
8716}
8717

8720    type GlibType = ffi::GtkPolicyType;
8721
8722    #[inline]
8723    fn into_glib(self) -> ffi::GtkPolicyType {
8724        match self {
8725            Self::Always => ffi::GTK_POLICY_ALWAYS,
8726            Self::Automatic => ffi::GTK_POLICY_AUTOMATIC,
8727            Self::Never => ffi::GTK_POLICY_NEVER,
8728            Self::External => ffi::GTK_POLICY_EXTERNAL,
8729            Self::__Unknown(value) => value,
8730        }
8731    }
8732}

9022/// Error codes that identify various errors that can occur while

9034    /// A memory allocation failed.

9156/// Determines what action the print operation should perform.
9157///

9270/// The result of a print operation.
9271///
9272/// A value of this type is returned by [`PrintOperationExt::run()`][crate::prelude::PrintOperationExt::run()].
9273#[derive(Debug, Eq, PartialEq, Ord, PartialOrd, Hash, Clone, Copy)]
9274#[non_exhaustive]
9275#[doc(alias = "GtkPrintOperationResult")]
9276pub enum PrintOperationResult {
9277    /// An error has occurred.
9278    #[doc(alias = "GTK_PRINT_OPERATION_RESULT_ERROR")]
9279    Error,
9280    /// The print settings should be stored.
9281    #[doc(alias = "GTK_PRINT_OPERATION_RESULT_APPLY")]
9282    Apply,
9283    /// The print operation has been canceled,
9284    ///   the print settings should not be stored.
9285    #[doc(alias = "GTK_PRINT_OPERATION_RESULT_CANCEL")]
9286    Cancel,
9287    /// The print operation is not complete
9288    ///   yet. This value will only be returned when running asynchronously.
9289    #[doc(alias = "GTK_PRINT_OPERATION_RESULT_IN_PROGRESS")]
9290    InProgress,
9291    #[doc(hidden)]
9292    __Unknown(i32),
9293}

9297    type GlibType = ffi::GtkPrintOperationResult;

9301        match self {
9302            Self::Error => ffi::GTK_PRINT_OPERATION_RESULT_ERROR,
9303            Self::Apply => ffi::GTK_PRINT_OPERATION_RESULT_APPLY,
9304            Self::Cancel => ffi::GTK_PRINT_OPERATION_RESULT_CANCEL,
9305            Self::InProgress => ffi::GTK_PRINT_OPERATION_RESULT_IN_PROGRESS,
9306            Self::__Unknown(value) => value,
9307        }
9308    }
9309}

9320            ffi::GTK_PRINT_OPERATION_RESULT_CANCEL => Self::Cancel,
9321            ffi::GTK_PRINT_OPERATION_RESULT_IN_PROGRESS => Self::InProgress,

9601/// The status gives a rough indication of the completion of a running
9602/// print operation.
9603#[derive(Debug, Eq, PartialEq, Ord, PartialOrd, Hash, Clone, Copy)]
9604#[non_exhaustive]
9605#[doc(alias = "GtkPrintStatus")]
9606pub enum PrintStatus {
9607    /// The printing has not started yet; this
9608    ///   status is set initially, and while the print dialog is shown.
9609    #[doc(alias = "GTK_PRINT_STATUS_INITIAL")]
9610    Initial,
9611    /// This status is set while the begin-print
9612    ///   signal is emitted and during pagination.
9613    #[doc(alias = "GTK_PRINT_STATUS_PREPARING")]
9614    Preparing,
9615    /// This status is set while the
9616    ///   pages are being rendered.
9617    #[doc(alias = "GTK_PRINT_STATUS_GENERATING_DATA")]
9618    GeneratingData,
9619    /// The print job is being sent off to the
9620    ///   printer.
9621    #[doc(alias = "GTK_PRINT_STATUS_SENDING_DATA")]
9622    SendingData,
9623    /// The print job has been sent to the printer,
9624    ///   but is not printed for some reason, e.g. the printer may be stopped.
9625    #[doc(alias = "GTK_PRINT_STATUS_PENDING")]
9626    Pending,
9627    /// Some problem has occurred during
9628    ///   printing, e.g. a paper jam.
9629    #[doc(alias = "GTK_PRINT_STATUS_PENDING_ISSUE")]
9630    PendingIssue,
9631    /// The printer is processing the print job.
9632    #[doc(alias = "GTK_PRINT_STATUS_PRINTING")]
9633    Printing,
9634    /// The printing has been completed successfully.
9635    #[doc(alias = "GTK_PRINT_STATUS_FINISHED")]
9636    Finished,
9637    /// The printing has been aborted.
9638    #[doc(alias = "GTK_PRINT_STATUS_FINISHED_ABORTED")]
9639    FinishedAborted,
9640    #[doc(hidden)]
9641    __Unknown(i32),
9642}

9653            Self::GeneratingData => ffi::GTK_PRINT_STATUS_GENERATING_DATA,
9654            Self::SendingData => ffi::GTK_PRINT_STATUS_SENDING_DATA,
9655            Self::Pending => ffi::GTK_PRINT_STATUS_PENDING,
9656            Self::PendingIssue => ffi::GTK_PRINT_STATUS_PENDING_ISSUE,
9657            Self::Printing => ffi::GTK_PRINT_STATUS_PRINTING,
9658            Self::Finished => ffi::GTK_PRINT_STATUS_FINISHED,
9659            Self::FinishedAborted => ffi::GTK_PRINT_STATUS_FINISHED_ABORTED,

9742/// Describes limits of a [`EventController`][crate::EventController] for handling events

9846/// Describes the stage at which events are fed into a [`EventController`][crate::EventController].
9847#[derive(Debug, Eq, PartialEq, Ord, PartialOrd, Hash, Clone, Copy)]
9848#[non_exhaustive]
9849#[doc(alias = "GtkPropagationPhase")]
9850pub enum PropagationPhase {
9851    /// Events are not delivered.
9852    #[doc(alias = "GTK_PHASE_NONE")]
9853    None,
9854    /// Events are delivered in the capture phase. The
9855    ///   capture phase happens before the bubble phase, runs from the toplevel down
9856    ///   to the event widget. This option should only be used on containers that
9857    ///   might possibly handle events before their children do.
9858    #[doc(alias = "GTK_PHASE_CAPTURE")]
9859    Capture,
9860    /// Events are delivered in the bubble phase. The bubble
9861    ///   phase happens after the capture phase, and before the default handlers
9862    ///   are run. This phase runs from the event widget, up to the toplevel.
9863    #[doc(alias = "GTK_PHASE_BUBBLE")]
9864    Bubble,
9865    /// Events are delivered in the default widget event handlers,
9866    ///   note that widget implementations must chain up on button, motion, touch and
9867    ///   grab broken handlers for controllers in this phase to be run.
9868    #[doc(alias = "GTK_PHASE_TARGET")]
9869    Target,
9870    #[doc(hidden)]
9871    __Unknown(i32),
9872}
9873
9874#[doc(hidden)]
9875impl IntoGlib for PropagationPhase {
9876    type GlibType = ffi::GtkPropagationPhase;
9877
9878    #[inline]
9879    fn into_glib(self) -> ffi::GtkPropagationPhase {
9880        match self {
9881            Self::None => ffi::GTK_PHASE_NONE,
9882            Self::Capture => ffi::GTK_PHASE_CAPTURE,
9883            Self::Bubble => ffi::GTK_PHASE_BUBBLE,
9884            Self::Target => ffi::GTK_PHASE_TARGET,
9885            Self::__Unknown(value) => value,
9886        }
9887    }
9888}
9889
9890#[doc(hidden)]
9891impl FromGlib<ffi::GtkPropagationPhase> for PropagationPhase {
9892    #[inline]
9893    unsafe fn from_glib(value: ffi::GtkPropagationPhase) -> Self {
9894        skip_assert_initialized!();
9895
9896        match value {
9897            ffi::GTK_PHASE_NONE => Self::None,
9898            ffi::GTK_PHASE_CAPTURE => Self::Capture,
9899            ffi::GTK_PHASE_BUBBLE => Self::Bubble,
9900            ffi::GTK_PHASE_TARGET => Self::Target,
9901            value => Self::__Unknown(value),
9902        }
9903    }
9904}

9907    #[inline]
9908    #[doc(alias = "gtk_propagation_phase_get_type")]

9918

10640/// Used to control what selections users are allowed to make.
10641#[derive(Debug, Eq, PartialEq, Ord, PartialOrd, Hash, Clone, Copy)]
10642#[non_exhaustive]
10643#[doc(alias = "GtkSelectionMode")]
10644pub enum SelectionMode {
10645    /// No selection is possible.
10646    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SELECTION_NONE")]
10647    None,
10648    /// Zero or one element may be selected.
10649    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SELECTION_SINGLE")]
10650    Single,
10651    /// Exactly one element is selected.
10652    ///   In some circumstances, such as initially or during a search
10653    ///   operation, it’s possible for no element to be selected with
10654    ///   [`Browse`][Self::Browse]. What is really enforced is that the user
10655    ///   can’t deselect a currently selected element except by selecting
10656    ///   another element.
10657    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SELECTION_BROWSE")]
10658    Browse,
10659    /// Any number of elements may be selected.
10660    ///   The Ctrl key may be used to enlarge the selection, and Shift
10661    ///   key to select between the focus and the child pointed to.
10662    ///   Some widgets may also allow Click-drag to select a range of elements.
10663    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SELECTION_MULTIPLE")]
10664    Multiple,
10665    #[doc(hidden)]
10666    __Unknown(i32),
10667}
10668

10671    type GlibType = ffi::GtkSelectionMode;
10672

10675        match self {
10676            Self::None => ffi::GTK_SELECTION_NONE,
10677            Self::Single => ffi::GTK_SELECTION_SINGLE,
10678            Self::Browse => ffi::GTK_SELECTION_BROWSE,
10679            Self::Multiple => ffi::GTK_SELECTION_MULTIPLE,
10680            Self::__Unknown(value) => value,
10681        }
10682    }

10863/// Describes where [`Shortcut`][crate::Shortcut]s added to a
10864/// [`ShortcutController`][crate::ShortcutController] get handled.
10865#[derive(Debug, Eq, PartialEq, Ord, PartialOrd, Hash, Clone, Copy)]

10893            Self::Managed => ffi::GTK_SHORTCUT_SCOPE_MANAGED,
10894            Self::Global => ffi::GTK_SHORTCUT_SCOPE_GLOBAL,

10971/// GtkShortcutType specifies the kind of shortcut that is being described.
10972///
10973/// More values may be added to this enumeration over time.
10974#[derive(Debug, Eq, PartialEq, Ord, PartialOrd, Hash, Clone, Copy)]
10975#[non_exhaustive]
10976#[doc(alias = "GtkShortcutType")]
10977pub enum ShortcutType {
10978    /// The shortcut is a keyboard accelerator. The GtkShortcutsShortcut:accelerator
10979    ///   property will be used.
10980    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SHORTCUT_ACCELERATOR")]
10981    Accelerator,
10982    /// The shortcut is a pinch gesture. GTK provides an icon and subtitle.
10983    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_PINCH")]
10984    GesturePinch,
10985    /// The shortcut is a stretch gesture. GTK provides an icon and subtitle.
10986    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_STRETCH")]
10987    GestureStretch,
10988    /// The shortcut is a clockwise rotation gesture. GTK provides an icon and subtitle.
10989    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_ROTATE_CLOCKWISE")]
10990    GestureRotateClockwise,
10991    /// The shortcut is a counterclockwise rotation gesture. GTK provides an icon and subtitle.
10992    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_ROTATE_COUNTERCLOCKWISE")]
10993    GestureRotateCounterclockwise,
10994    /// The shortcut is a two-finger swipe gesture. GTK provides an icon and subtitle.
10995    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_TWO_FINGER_SWIPE_LEFT")]
10996    GestureTwoFingerSwipeLeft,
10997    /// The shortcut is a two-finger swipe gesture. GTK provides an icon and subtitle.
10998    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_TWO_FINGER_SWIPE_RIGHT")]
10999    GestureTwoFingerSwipeRight,
11000    /// The shortcut is a gesture. The GtkShortcutsShortcut:icon property will be
11001    ///   used.
11002    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE")]
11003    Gesture,
11004    /// The shortcut is a swipe gesture. GTK provides an icon and subtitle.
11005    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_SWIPE_LEFT")]
11006    GestureSwipeLeft,
11007    /// The shortcut is a swipe gesture. GTK provides an icon and subtitle.
11008    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_SWIPE_RIGHT")]
11009    GestureSwipeRight,
11010    #[doc(hidden)]
11011    __Unknown(i32),
11012}
11013
11014#[doc(hidden)]
11015impl IntoGlib for ShortcutType {
11016    type GlibType = ffi::GtkShortcutType;
11017
11018    #[inline]
11019    fn into_glib(self) -> ffi::GtkShortcutType {
11020        match self {
11021            Self::Accelerator => ffi::GTK_SHORTCUT_ACCELERATOR,
11022            Self::GesturePinch => ffi::GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_PINCH,
11023            Self::GestureStretch => ffi::GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_STRETCH,
11024            Self::GestureRotateClockwise => ffi::GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_ROTATE_CLOCKWISE,
11025            Self::GestureRotateCounterclockwise => {
11026                ffi::GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_ROTATE_COUNTERCLOCKWISE
11027            }
11028            Self::GestureTwoFingerSwipeLeft => ffi::GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_TWO_FINGER_SWIPE_LEFT,
11029            Self::GestureTwoFingerSwipeRight => ffi::GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_TWO_FINGER_SWIPE_RIGHT,
11030            Self::Gesture => ffi::GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE,
11031            Self::GestureSwipeLeft => ffi::GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_SWIPE_LEFT,
11032            Self::GestureSwipeRight => ffi::GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_SWIPE_RIGHT,
11033            Self::__Unknown(value) => value,
11034        }
11035    }
11036}

11042        skip_assert_initialized!();
11043
11044        match value {
11045            ffi::GTK_SHORTCUT_ACCELERATOR => Self::Accelerator,
11046            ffi::GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_PINCH => Self::GesturePinch,
11047            ffi::GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_STRETCH => Self::GestureStretch,
11048            ffi::GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_ROTATE_CLOCKWISE => Self::GestureRotateClockwise,
11049            ffi::GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_ROTATE_COUNTERCLOCKWISE => {
11050                Self::GestureRotateCounterclockwise
11051            }
11052            ffi::GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_TWO_FINGER_SWIPE_LEFT => Self::GestureTwoFingerSwipeLeft,
11053            ffi::GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_TWO_FINGER_SWIPE_RIGHT => Self::GestureTwoFingerSwipeRight,
11054            ffi::GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE => Self::Gesture,
11055            ffi::GTK_SHORTCUT_GESTURE_SWIPE_LEFT => Self::GestureSwipeLeft,

11432/// Describes changes in a sorter in more detail and allows users
11433/// to optimize resorting.
11434#[derive(Debug, Eq, PartialEq, Ord, PartialOrd, Hash, Clone, Copy)]
11435#[non_exhaustive]
11436#[doc(alias = "GtkSorterChange")]
11437pub enum SorterChange {
11438    /// The sorter change cannot be described
11439    ///   by any of the other enumeration values
11440    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SORTER_CHANGE_DIFFERENT")]
11441    Different,
11442    /// The sort order was inverted. Comparisons
11443    ///   that returned [`Ordering::Smaller`][crate::Ordering::Smaller] now return [`Ordering::Larger`][crate::Ordering::Larger]
11444    ///   and vice versa. Other comparisons return the same values as before.
11445    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SORTER_CHANGE_INVERTED")]
11446    Inverted,
11447    /// The sorter is less strict: Comparisons
11448    ///   may now return [`Ordering::Equal`][crate::Ordering::Equal] that did not do so before.
11449    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SORTER_CHANGE_LESS_STRICT")]
11450    LessStrict,
11451    /// The sorter is more strict: Comparisons
11452    ///   that did return [`Ordering::Equal`][crate::Ordering::Equal] may not do so anymore.
11453    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SORTER_CHANGE_MORE_STRICT")]
11454    MoreStrict,
11455    #[doc(hidden)]
11456    __Unknown(i32),
11457}
11458
11459#[doc(hidden)]
11460impl IntoGlib for SorterChange {
11461    type GlibType = ffi::GtkSorterChange;
11462
11463    #[inline]
11464    fn into_glib(self) -> ffi::GtkSorterChange {
11465        match self {
11466            Self::Different => ffi::GTK_SORTER_CHANGE_DIFFERENT,
11467            Self::Inverted => ffi::GTK_SORTER_CHANGE_INVERTED,
11468            Self::LessStrict => ffi::GTK_SORTER_CHANGE_LESS_STRICT,
11469            Self::MoreStrict => ffi::GTK_SORTER_CHANGE_MORE_STRICT,
11470            Self::__Unknown(value) => value,
11471        }
11472    }
11473}

11480
11481        match value {
11482            ffi::GTK_SORTER_CHANGE_DIFFERENT => Self::Different,
11483            ffi::GTK_SORTER_CHANGE_INVERTED => Self::Inverted,
11484            ffi::GTK_SORTER_CHANGE_LESS_STRICT => Self::LessStrict,
11485            ffi::GTK_SORTER_CHANGE_MORE_STRICT => Self::MoreStrict,

11547/// Describes the type of order that a [`Sorter`][crate::Sorter] may produce.
11548#[derive(Debug, Eq, PartialEq, Ord, PartialOrd, Hash, Clone, Copy)]
11549#[non_exhaustive]
11550#[doc(alias = "GtkSorterOrder")]
11551pub enum SorterOrder {
11552    /// A partial order. Any [`Ordering`][crate::Ordering] is possible.
11553    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SORTER_ORDER_PARTIAL")]
11554    Partial,
11555    /// No order, all elements are considered equal.
11556    ///   gtk_sorter_compare() will only return [`Ordering::Equal`][crate::Ordering::Equal].
11557    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SORTER_ORDER_NONE")]
11558    None,
11559    /// A total order. gtk_sorter_compare() will only
11560    ///   return [`Ordering::Equal`][crate::Ordering::Equal] if an item is compared with itself. Two
11561    ///   different items will never cause this value to be returned.
11562    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SORTER_ORDER_TOTAL")]
11563    Total,
11564    #[doc(hidden)]
11565    __Unknown(i32),
11566}

11570    type GlibType = ffi::GtkSorterOrder;

11574        match self {
11575            Self::Partial => ffi::GTK_SORTER_ORDER_PARTIAL,
11576            Self::None => ffi::GTK_SORTER_ORDER_NONE,
11577            Self::Total => ffi::GTK_SORTER_ORDER_TOTAL,
11578            Self::__Unknown(value) => value,
11579        }
11580    }
11581}
11582

11759/// The values of the GtkSpinType enumeration are used to specify the
11760/// change to make in gtk_spin_button_spin().
11761#[derive(Debug, Eq, PartialEq, Ord, PartialOrd, Hash, Clone, Copy)]
11762#[non_exhaustive]
11763#[doc(alias = "GtkSpinType")]
11764pub enum SpinType {
11765    /// Increment by the adjustments step increment.
11766    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SPIN_STEP_FORWARD")]
11767    StepForward,
11768    /// Decrement by the adjustments step increment.
11769    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SPIN_STEP_BACKWARD")]
11770    StepBackward,
11771    /// Increment by the adjustments page increment.
11772    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SPIN_PAGE_FORWARD")]
11773    PageForward,
11774    /// Decrement by the adjustments page increment.
11775    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SPIN_PAGE_BACKWARD")]
11776    PageBackward,
11777    /// Go to the adjustments lower bound.
11778    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SPIN_HOME")]
11779    Home,
11780    /// Go to the adjustments upper bound.
11781    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SPIN_END")]
11782    End,
11783    /// Change by a specified amount.
11784    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SPIN_USER_DEFINED")]
11785    UserDefined,
11786    #[doc(hidden)]
11787    __Unknown(i32),
11788}
11789
11790#[doc(hidden)]
11791impl IntoGlib for SpinType {
11792    type GlibType = ffi::GtkSpinType;
11793
11794    #[inline]
11795    fn into_glib(self) -> ffi::GtkSpinType {
11796        match self {
11797            Self::StepForward => ffi::GTK_SPIN_STEP_FORWARD,
11798            Self::StepBackward => ffi::GTK_SPIN_STEP_BACKWARD,
11799            Self::PageForward => ffi::GTK_SPIN_PAGE_FORWARD,
11800            Self::PageBackward => ffi::GTK_SPIN_PAGE_BACKWARD,
11801            Self::Home => ffi::GTK_SPIN_HOME,
11802            Self::End => ffi::GTK_SPIN_END,
11803            Self::UserDefined => ffi::GTK_SPIN_USER_DEFINED,
11804            Self::__Unknown(value) => value,
11805        }
11806    }
11807}

11884/// Possible transitions between pages in a [`Stack`][crate::Stack] widget.
11885///
11886/// New values may be added to this enumeration over time.
11887#[derive(Debug, Eq, PartialEq, Ord, PartialOrd, Hash, Clone, Copy)]
11888#[non_exhaustive]
11889#[doc(alias = "GtkStackTransitionType")]
11890pub enum StackTransitionType {
11891    /// No transition
11892    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_NONE")]
11893    None,
11894    /// A cross-fade
11895    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_CROSSFADE")]
11896    Crossfade,
11897    /// Slide from left to right
11898    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_SLIDE_RIGHT")]
11899    SlideRight,
11900    /// Slide from right to left
11901    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_SLIDE_LEFT")]
11902    SlideLeft,
11903    /// Slide from bottom up
11904    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_SLIDE_UP")]
11905    SlideUp,
11906    /// Slide from top down
11907    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_SLIDE_DOWN")]
11908    SlideDown,
11909    /// Slide from left or right according to the children order
11910    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_SLIDE_LEFT_RIGHT")]
11911    SlideLeftRight,
11912    /// Slide from top down or bottom up according to the order
11913    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_SLIDE_UP_DOWN")]
11914    SlideUpDown,
11915    /// Cover the old page by sliding up
11916    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_OVER_UP")]
11917    OverUp,
11918    /// Cover the old page by sliding down
11919    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_OVER_DOWN")]
11920    OverDown,
11921    /// Cover the old page by sliding to the left
11922    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_OVER_LEFT")]
11923    OverLeft,
11924    /// Cover the old page by sliding to the right
11925    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_OVER_RIGHT")]
11926    OverRight,
11927    /// Uncover the new page by sliding up
11928    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_UNDER_UP")]
11929    UnderUp,
11930    /// Uncover the new page by sliding down
11931    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_UNDER_DOWN")]
11932    UnderDown,
11933    /// Uncover the new page by sliding to the left
11934    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_UNDER_LEFT")]
11935    UnderLeft,
11936    /// Uncover the new page by sliding to the right
11937    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_UNDER_RIGHT")]
11938    UnderRight,
11939    /// Cover the old page sliding up or uncover the new page sliding down, according to order
11940    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_OVER_UP_DOWN")]
11941    OverUpDown,
11942    /// Cover the old page sliding down or uncover the new page sliding up, according to order
11943    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_OVER_DOWN_UP")]
11944    OverDownUp,
11945    /// Cover the old page sliding left or uncover the new page sliding right, according to order
11946    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_OVER_LEFT_RIGHT")]
11947    OverLeftRight,
11948    /// Cover the old page sliding right or uncover the new page sliding left, according to order
11949    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_OVER_RIGHT_LEFT")]
11950    OverRightLeft,
11951    /// Pretend the pages are sides of a cube and rotate that cube to the left
11952    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_ROTATE_LEFT")]
11953    RotateLeft,
11954    /// Pretend the pages are sides of a cube and rotate that cube to the right
11955    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_ROTATE_RIGHT")]
11956    RotateRight,
11957    /// Pretend the pages are sides of a cube and rotate that cube to the left or right according to the children order
11958    #[doc(alias = "GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_ROTATE_LEFT_RIGHT")]
11959    RotateLeftRight,
11960    #[doc(hidden)]
11961    __Unknown(i32),
11962}
11963

11970            Self::None => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_NONE,
11971            Self::Crossfade => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_CROSSFADE,
11972            Self::SlideRight => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_SLIDE_RIGHT,
11973            Self::SlideLeft => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_SLIDE_LEFT,
11974            Self::SlideUp => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_SLIDE_UP,
11975            Self::SlideDown => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_SLIDE_DOWN,
11976            Self::SlideLeftRight => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_SLIDE_LEFT_RIGHT,
11977            Self::SlideUpDown => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_SLIDE_UP_DOWN,
11978            Self::OverUp => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_OVER_UP,
11979            Self::OverDown => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_OVER_DOWN,
11980            Self::OverLeft => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_OVER_LEFT,
11981            Self::OverRight => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_OVER_RIGHT,
11982            Self::UnderUp => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_UNDER_UP,
11983            Self::UnderDown => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_UNDER_DOWN,
11984            Self::UnderLeft => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_UNDER_LEFT,
11985            Self::UnderRight => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_UNDER_RIGHT,
11986            Self::OverUpDown => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_OVER_UP_DOWN,
11987            Self::OverDownUp => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_OVER_DOWN_UP,
11988            Self::OverLeftRight => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_OVER_LEFT_RIGHT,
11989            Self::OverRightLeft => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_OVER_RIGHT_LEFT,
11990            Self::RotateLeft => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_ROTATE_LEFT,
11991            Self::RotateRight => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_ROTATE_RIGHT,
11992            Self::RotateLeftRight => ffi::GTK_STACK_TRANSITION_TYPE_ROTATE_LEFT_RIGHT,
11993            Self::__Unknown(value) => value,

11995    }

12325/// Values that can be passed to the [`WidgetImpl::system_setting_changed()`][crate::subclass::prelude::WidgetImpl::system_setting_changed()]
12326/// vfunc.
12327///
12328/// The values indicate which system setting has changed.
12329/// Widgets may need to drop caches, or react otherwise.
12330///
12331/// Most of the values correspond to [`Settings`][crate::Settings] properties.
12332///
12333/// More values may be added over time.
12334#[derive(Debug, Eq, PartialEq, Ord, PartialOrd, Hash, Clone, Copy)]
12335#[non_exhaustive]
12336#[doc(alias = "GtkSystemSetting")]
12337pub enum SystemSetting {
12338    /// the [`gtk-xft-dpi`][struct@crate::Settings#gtk-xft-dpi] setting has changed
12339    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SYSTEM_SETTING_DPI")]
12340    Dpi,
12341    /// The [`gtk-font-name`][struct@crate::Settings#gtk-font-name] setting has changed
12342    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SYSTEM_SETTING_FONT_NAME")]
12343    FontName,
12344    /// The font configuration has changed in a way that
12345    ///   requires text to be redrawn. This can be any of the
12346    ///   [`gtk-xft-antialias`][struct@crate::Settings#gtk-xft-antialias],
12347    ///   [`gtk-xft-hinting`][struct@crate::Settings#gtk-xft-hinting],
12348    ///   [`gtk-xft-hintstyle`][struct@crate::Settings#gtk-xft-hintstyle],
12349    ///   [`gtk-xft-rgba`][struct@crate::Settings#gtk-xft-rgba] or
12350    ///   [`gtk-fontconfig-timestamp`][struct@crate::Settings#gtk-fontconfig-timestamp] settings
12351    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SYSTEM_SETTING_FONT_CONFIG")]
12352    FontConfig,
12353    /// The display has changed
12354    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SYSTEM_SETTING_DISPLAY")]
12355    Display,
12356    /// The icon theme has changed in a way that requires
12357    ///   icons to be looked up again
12358    #[doc(alias = "GTK_SYSTEM_SETTING_ICON_THEME")]
12359    IconTheme,
12360    #[doc(hidden)]
12361    __Unknown(i32),
12362}
12363
12364#[doc(hidden)]
12365impl IntoGlib for SystemSetting {
12366    type GlibType = ffi::GtkSystemSetting;
12367
12368    #[inline]
12369    fn into_glib(self) -> ffi::GtkSystemSetting {
12370        match self {
12371            Self::Dpi => ffi::GTK_SYSTEM_SETTING_DPI,
12372            Self::FontName => ffi::GTK_SYSTEM_SETTING_FONT_NAME,
12373            Self::FontConfig => ffi::GTK_SYSTEM_SETTING_FONT_CONFIG,
12374            Self::Display => ffi::GTK_SYSTEM_SETTING_DISPLAY,
12375            Self::IconTheme => ffi::GTK_SYSTEM_SETTING_ICON_THEME,
12376            Self::__Unknown(value) => value,
12377        }
12378    }
12379}
12380
12381#[doc(hidden)]
12382impl FromGlib<ffi::GtkSystemSetting> for SystemSetting {
12383    #[inline]
12384    unsafe fn from_glib(value: ffi::GtkSystemSetting) -> Self {
12385        skip_assert_initialized!();
12386
12387        match value {
12388            ffi::GTK_SYSTEM_SETTING_DPI => Self::Dpi,
12389            ffi::GTK_SYSTEM_SETTING_FONT_NAME => Self::FontName,
12390            ffi::GTK_SYSTEM_SETTING_FONT_CONFIG => Self::FontConfig,
12391            ffi::GTK_SYSTEM_SETTING_DISPLAY => Self::Display,
12392            ffi::GTK_SYSTEM_SETTING_ICON_THEME => Self::IconTheme,
12393            value => Self::__Unknown(value),
12394        }
12395    }
12396}

12879/// The sizing method the column uses to determine its width.  Please note
12880/// that [`Autosize`][Self::Autosize] are inefficient for large views, and
12881/// can make columns appear choppy.
12882///
12883/// # Deprecated since 4.20
12884///
12885/// There is no replacement.
12886#[cfg_attr(feature = "v4_20", deprecated = "Since 4.20")]
12887#[derive(Debug, Eq, PartialEq, Ord, PartialOrd, Hash, Clone, Copy)]
12888#[non_exhaustive]
12889#[doc(alias = "GtkTreeViewColumnSizing")]
12890pub enum TreeViewColumnSizing {
12891    /// Columns only get bigger in reaction to changes in the model
12892    #[doc(alias = "GTK_TREE_VIEW_COLUMN_GROW_ONLY")]
12893    GrowOnly,
12894    /// Columns resize to be the optimal size every time the model changes.
12895    #[doc(alias = "GTK_TREE_VIEW_COLUMN_AUTOSIZE")]
12896    Autosize,
12897    /// Columns are a fixed numbers of pixels wide.
12898    #[doc(alias = "GTK_TREE_VIEW_COLUMN_FIXED")]
12899    Fixed,
12900    #[doc(hidden)]
12901    __Unknown(i32),
12902}
12903

12905#[doc(hidden)]
12906impl IntoGlib for TreeViewColumnSizing {
12907    type GlibType = ffi::GtkTreeViewColumnSizing;
12908
12909    #[inline]
12910    fn into_glib(self) -> ffi::GtkTreeViewColumnSizing {
12911        match self {
12912            Self::GrowOnly => ffi::GTK_TREE_VIEW_COLUMN_GROW_ONLY,
12913            Self::Autosize => ffi::GTK_TREE_VIEW_COLUMN_AUTOSIZE,
12914            Self::Fixed => ffi::GTK_TREE_VIEW_COLUMN_FIXED,
12915            Self::__Unknown(value) => value,
12916        }
12917    }
12918}

12998/// An enum for determining where a dropped row goes.

13351/// Determines which point or edge of a window is meant to remain fixed
13352/// when a window changes size.
13353#[cfg(feature = "v4_20")]
13354#[cfg_attr(docsrs, doc(cfg(feature = "v4_20")))]
13355#[derive(Debug, Eq, PartialEq, Ord, PartialOrd, Hash, Clone, Copy)]
13356#[non_exhaustive]
13357#[doc(alias = "GtkWindowGravity")]
13358pub enum WindowGravity {
13359    /// The top left corner
13360    #[doc(alias = "GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_TOP_LEFT")]
13361    TopLeft,
13362    /// The top edge
13363    #[doc(alias = "GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_TOP")]
13364    Top,
13365    /// The top right corner
13366    #[doc(alias = "GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_TOP_RIGHT")]
13367    TopRight,
13368    /// The left edge
13369    #[doc(alias = "GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_LEFT")]
13370    Left,
13371    /// The center pointer
13372    #[doc(alias = "GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_CENTER")]
13373    Center,
13374    /// The right edge
13375    #[doc(alias = "GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_RIGHT")]
13376    Right,
13377    /// The bottom left corner
13378    #[doc(alias = "GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_BOTTOM_LEFT")]
13379    BottomLeft,
13380    /// the bottom edge
13381    #[doc(alias = "GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_BOTTOM")]
13382    Bottom,
13383    /// The bottom right corner
13384    #[doc(alias = "GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_BOTTOM_RIGHT")]
13385    BottomRight,
13386    /// The top left or top right corner,
13387    ///   depending on the text direction
13388    #[doc(alias = "GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_TOP_START")]
13389    TopStart,
13390    /// The top right or top left corner,
13391    ///   depending on the text direction
13392    #[doc(alias = "GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_TOP_END")]
13393    TopEnd,
13394    /// The left or right edge,
13395    ///   depending on the text direction
13396    #[doc(alias = "GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_START")]
13397    Start,
13398    /// The right or left edge,
13399    ///   depending on the text direction
13400    #[doc(alias = "GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_END")]
13401    End,
13402    /// The bottom left or top right corner,
13403    ///   depending on the text direction
13404    #[doc(alias = "GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_BOTTOM_START")]
13405    BottomStart,
13406    /// The bottom right or top left corner,
13407    ///   depending on the text direction
13408    #[doc(alias = "GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_BOTTOM_END")]
13409    BottomEnd,
13410    #[doc(hidden)]
13411    __Unknown(i32),
13412}
13413
13414#[cfg(feature = "v4_20")]
13415#[cfg_attr(docsrs, doc(cfg(feature = "v4_20")))]
13416#[doc(hidden)]
13417impl IntoGlib for WindowGravity {
13418    type GlibType = ffi::GtkWindowGravity;
13419
13420    fn into_glib(self) -> ffi::GtkWindowGravity {
13421        match self {
13422            Self::TopLeft => ffi::GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_TOP_LEFT,
13423            Self::Top => ffi::GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_TOP,
13424            Self::TopRight => ffi::GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_TOP_RIGHT,
13425            Self::Left => ffi::GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_LEFT,
13426            Self::Center => ffi::GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_CENTER,
13427            Self::Right => ffi::GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_RIGHT,
13428            Self::BottomLeft => ffi::GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_BOTTOM_LEFT,
13429            Self::Bottom => ffi::GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_BOTTOM,
13430            Self::BottomRight => ffi::GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_BOTTOM_RIGHT,
13431            Self::TopStart => ffi::GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_TOP_START,
13432            Self::TopEnd => ffi::GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_TOP_END,
13433            Self::Start => ffi::GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_START,
13434            Self::End => ffi::GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_END,
13435            Self::BottomStart => ffi::GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_BOTTOM_START,
13436            Self::BottomEnd => ffi::GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_BOTTOM_END,
13437            Self::__Unknown(value) => value,
13438        }
13439    }
13440}

13460            ffi::GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_TOP_END => Self::TopEnd,
13461            ffi::GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_START => Self::Start,
13462            ffi::GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_END => Self::End,
13463            ffi::GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_BOTTOM_START => Self::BottomStart,
13464            ffi::GTK_WINDOW_GRAVITY_BOTTOM_END => Self::BottomEnd,
13465            value => Self::__Unknown(value),
13466        }
13467    }
13468}

13538/// Describes a type of line wrapping.
13539#[derive(Debug, Eq, PartialEq, Ord, PartialOrd, Hash, Clone, Copy)]
13540#[non_exhaustive]
13541#[doc(alias = "GtkWrapMode")]
13542pub enum WrapMode {
13543    /// do not wrap lines; just make the text area wider
13544    #[doc(alias = "GTK_WRAP_NONE")]
13545    None,
13546    /// wrap text, breaking lines anywhere the cursor can
13547    ///   appear (between characters, usually - if you want to be technical,
13548    ///   between graphemes, see pango_get_log_attrs())
13549    #[doc(alias = "GTK_WRAP_CHAR")]
13550    Char,
13551    /// wrap text, breaking lines in between words
13552    #[doc(alias = "GTK_WRAP_WORD")]
13553    Word,
13554    /// wrap text, breaking lines in between words, or if
13555    ///   that is not enough, also between graphemes
13556    #[doc(alias = "GTK_WRAP_WORD_CHAR")]
13557    WordChar,
13558    #[doc(hidden)]
13559    __Unknown(i32),
13560}
13561
13562#[doc(hidden)]
13563impl IntoGlib for WrapMode {
13564    type GlibType = ffi::GtkWrapMode;
13565
13566    #[inline]
13567    fn into_glib(self) -> ffi::GtkWrapMode {
13568        match self {
13569            Self::None => ffi::GTK_WRAP_NONE,
13570            Self::Char => ffi::GTK_WRAP_CHAR,
13571            Self::Word => ffi::GTK_WRAP_WORD,
13572            Self::WordChar => ffi::GTK_WRAP_WORD_CHAR,
13573            Self::__Unknown(value) => value,
13574        }
13575    }
13576}
13577
13578#[doc(hidden)]
13579impl FromGlib<ffi::GtkWrapMode> for WrapMode {
13580    #[inline]
13581    unsafe fn from_glib(value: ffi::GtkWrapMode) -> Self {
13582        skip_assert_initialized!();
13583
13584        match value {
13585            ffi::GTK_WRAP_NONE => Self::None,
13586            ffi::GTK_WRAP_CHAR => Self::Char,
13587            ffi::GTK_WRAP_WORD => Self::Word,
13588            ffi::GTK_WRAP_WORD_CHAR => Self::WordChar,
13589            value => Self::__Unknown(value),
13590        }
13591    }
13592}
13593
13594impl StaticType for WrapMode {
13595    #[inline]
13596    #[doc(alias = "gtk_wrap_mode_get_type")]
13597    fn static_type() -> glib::Type {
13598        unsafe { from_glib(ffi::gtk_wrap_mode_get_type()) }
13599    }
13600}
